Job Description
Main Duties / Key Responsibilities:Write legendary, high- performance, scalable, and maintainable codeAnalyze, propose and develop solutions for our search architectureHelp lead architectural design of complex distributed systemsCommunicate effectively with other teams inside and outside engineeringLead projects, mentor junior engineers, and help recruit top tier talent.Monitors all source code changes using standard source control (PVCS)Assists analysts in understanding how code changes affect the applicationsDemonstrates and applies a knowledge and understanding of development tools at their level of experience ( junior, developer, or senior)Demonstrates and applies a knowledge and understanding of applicable languages at their level of experience ( junior, developer, or senior)Explains technical concepts effectively, taking audience into accountCommunicates effectively with Technical and Business Systems AnalystsConsistently creates and executes unit test plans appropriate to the taskUnderstands and comprehends design requirements as specifiedProvide guidance and mentoring for junior engineers hired into the team who may be tasked to perform some of the above duties.Requirements: Educational, Knowledge, Skills and ExperienceMust have a bachelor`s degree in Computer Science/ Engineering or equivalentSkills - JBOSS Application Server, J2EE, JBOSS Portal, Open Source Java Frameworks e. g. Struts/ Spring/ JSF/ Hibernate etc., Java development tools, XML, JUNIT, MQSeries, etc. Experience with databases is an added advantage.Must have experience in DOJOSolid understanding of Server side Java development, experience on Service Oriented Architectures and enterprise level integrationsExcellent communication/ mentoring skills.This individual will be a key member in the engineering teamMust have superior problem solving skillsExperience with full lifecycle development projects, OO/ SOA RUP. Experience developing products is an added advantage
